Our first HIP CARRY TUTORIAL for The Loop Carrier is here! ➰

Watch this 10-minute video hosted by our babywearing educator, Morgan, as she demonstrates how to comfortably, confidently, and safely hip carry your growing babe in the Loop! Woohoo! 💫

Feel free to ask any questions below and she will hop in and answer. 👇

node.text: And once you embrace this, it's LIBERATING. 🙌🏼 The shift in expectations changes *everything* and suddenly you're not annoyed that you haven't read a single chapter of your novel📗 or slept past 7 am💤 (or 5:30 am🤪) but instead thrilled that you're rocking baby to sleep listening to the waves of a real ocean🌊 (that don't come from a sound machine! 😂) or pulling over to change a diaper in the back of the car with jaw-dropping mountains⛰ as the backdrop, or simply picking up carryout🍱 from somewhere other than your neighborhood pizza joint🍕 that you've ordered from 100x in the past year. It's all about perspective, you know? ✨

node.text:
When mamas ask how many wraps they need…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I always recommend two—one print + one solid. ✌🏽 The print makes even a basic tee feel pulled together; the solid goes with literally everything. And most importantly, having a second means you’re not in a bind when baby has a blowout 💩 and you have to toss one in the wash midday. Bc we’ve ALL been there, amirite? 🙋🏽‍♀️

node.text: 💡Did you know that wrap time counts as tummy time? (But is, like, way more cozy and well-received. 😂) Babies loooove to look up at you and may even push off on your chest while in the wrap. It’s not a sign they’re uncomfortable! It’s actually a common developmental milestone that works all of their neck, back, arm and core muscles in preparation for eventually pushing up and rolling over. In other words, babywearing is basically a super snuggly workout for both of you. ☁️💪🏽
